<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/4–2849</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation With the President, by
                                    the Secretary of State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-28">April 28,
                                    1949</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="flushleft">
                                <hi rend="italic">Item No. 2—Letter from Dr. Weizmann</hi>
                            </p>
                            <p>The President showed me a letter from Dr. Weizmann,<note n="1" xml:id="d614fn1">Dated April 26, <ref target="#pg_947">p.
                                        947</ref>.</note> a copy of which will come to us today.</p>
                            <p>The letter referred to a request that we assist by talking with other
                                members of the United Nations on the subject of admission of Israel
                                to the United Nations. The President agreed that Dr. Weizmann’s
                                attitude on refugees was not satisfactory and thought that we were
                                not in a position to bring pressure on other members of the United
                                Nations.</p>
                            <p>I related to the President my last meeting with Ambassador Elath and
                                Mr. Eban.<note n="2" xml:id="d614fn2">See Secretary Acheson’s
                                    memorandum of conversation, April 26, <ref target="#pg_944">p.
                                        944</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>